About this item

  • Ultra 2K Resolution & Advanced Night VisionGalayou indoor camera wireless with 2K HD resolution provides you a clear and vivid image quality and captures more details on your home anywhere during day and night by using 6X digital Zoom. Enhanced night vision with effective distance up to 33 ft . This indoor camera for home security only supports 2.4GHz WiFi. ( 5GHz is not supported )
  • 24/7 Real-Time Motion Alert & Smart Siren The nanny cam supports instant detection and push alert to monitor your baby/pet/garage. When your baby is climbing out of the cribs or your garage door is opened, Galayou baby camera monitor will send alert message on your phone to let you know.
  • Remote Monitoring & Two-Way Audio Built-in microphone and speaker allows you to keep in touch with your baby, pet, family by remotely controlling the Wansview Cloud APP when you are out or traveling. This WiFi camera for home surveillance also can scare away the unexpected intruder to keep your property safe with audio feature.
  • Secure Local Storage & Cloud Storage 24/7 continuous recording feature is open to all Galayou customers without extra fees. Galayou indoor camera supports up to 128GB mciro SD card to store the vidoe clips on local storage. The Cloud storage also is a good option for the user who don't want to take the risk of losing card and card damaged. All recorded videos will be fully protected and encrypted with AWS Cloud.
  • Works with Alexa& Google Home The security camera indoor wireless is compatible with Alexa and Google home. Just use the voice command to control these devices to show you the live-feed of camera. The smart integration between the Galayou camera and your device make your home system more intelligent and reliable.

      • Are they battery cameras?

        No. They are powered by the Type-C cable.

      • Does it connect to the 5ghz wifi?

        No. It only connects with 2.4ghz wifi. You can check if the router supports 2.4ghz wifi first.

      • Do I have to pay the cloud service?

        No. The cloud service is optional and can be replaced by SD card (not included). The motion alert function is free to use.

      • What if I can't connect the camera?

        Firstly, please confirm you have turned on 2.4ghz wifi. Then please ensure the indicator light is flashing blue twice (which means the camera is ready for connection) before you scan the QR code.

      • What if a SD card is inserted but not recognized?

        If you insert a SD card but no memory card storage function, you can format the card to FAT 32; try another SD card; restart the camera and update its firmware.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      • Yossarian Xander
        4.0 out of 5 stars A great product with room for improvement.
        Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
        Size: 1 Count (Pack of 1)Verified Purchase
        Im very pleased with the functionality of such a little thing at such a low price. It provides 2K resolution that is much better than my big old ones, night vision, motion detection, motion alert, family sharing, voice communication and more. Most of the features I have tested work well. One major issue is with the voice feature. When I tap the call button, it starts with a loud noise that lasts several seconds before it reduces to constant low noise level at that the communication can be started. In addition, motion-activated recording is hit or miss. I kept moving and counting numbers loud in front of the camera for about 1 minute. When I only made small moves, it sent one notification to my phone and only recorded less than 10 seconds for the beginning part. When I kept making significant move all the time, it sent two notifications and recorded 5 clips for about 4 to 10 seconds each. Based on the numbers I count, it missed at least 20 seconds or one third of the event. The setup is very easy, even for a layman. The service was great. I ordered two units. One makes constant noise but the other doesnt under exactly same conditions. I sent an email with a video (its very easy to record videos and take photos manually through the app) attached to service@wansview.com asking for helping solve the problem. I was told its a hardware problem and several days later I received a replacement. However, all the three units have the communication noise issue that I believe exists for all their products. If you need to communicate with someone through the camera, you may want to make sure the problem has been solved before you buy it. To me, this is a great product with room for improvement and Im glad I bought it.
